## Setting up a Development Environment
To start building your voting dApp, we need to set up our development environment. Here's what you'll need:

### Tools Required:
- Node.js: JavaScript runtime environment.
- npm: Node package manager.
- Truffle: Ethereum development framework.
- Ganache: Local blockchain for testing.
- MetaMask: Ethereum wallet browser extension.
#### Step-by-Step Setup:
- Install Node.js and npm:

Download and install Node.js from nodejs.org. This will also install npm.
- Install Truffle:

Open your terminal and run:
```
npm install -g truffle
```
- Install Ganache:

Download and install Ganache from trufflesuite.com/ganache.
- Install MetaMask:

Add the MetaMask extension to your browser from metamask.io.


